      <hedline>
        <hl1>Call It Global Heating</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mel Sokotch letter says phrase 'global warming' does not sound threatening; suggests renaming problem 'global heating' might help focus attention (April 23 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Yelling 'Fire' on a Hot Planet'' (Week in Review, April 23):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Yelling 'Fire' on a Hot Planet'' (Week in Review, April 23):</p>
        <p>One reason global warming ranks so low on the list of environmental concerns might be the phrase itself: ''global warming'' just doesn't sound all that threatening.</p>
        <p>Let's rephrase the problem as ''global heating.'' This is no less accurate, but sounds more distressing and might help focus attention.</p>
        <p>Mel Sokotch  New York, April 23, 2006</p>
        <p>The writer is an advertising executive.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
